---
# Starter taxonomy template — emitted by the SAI onboarding wizard.
#
# COPY this file to `prompts/email/keyword-classify.md` and edit:
#   - replace the placeholder buckets with 5-7 categories that match
#     how YOU actually sort email today
#   - for each bucket, list a few SENDER patterns (full addresses or
#     bare domains) that should ALWAYS land there
#   - keep `no_label` (or rename it) as the catch-all fallback
#
# All example domains below use the IETF reserved `example.com` /
# `example.org` / `test` namespaces. Substitute real domains only in
# your private operator overlay, never in the public repo.
#
# This file is a STARTER. Once your taxonomy is firing well you can
# move richer rules (regex, header matches, label-overrides) into a
# proper skill manifest — see `app/skills/sample_echo_skill/skill.yaml`
# for the full plug-in protocol shape (PRINCIPLES.md §33).

prompt_id: keyword_email_classifier_starter_example
version: "1"
description: |
  Multi-bucket keyword-classifier template. Replace the placeholder
  buckets below with your real categories before deploying.

classifier:
  # ---- bucket 1: customers ----
  customers_sender_emails: []
  customers_sender_domains:
    - customer-a.example.com
    - customer-b.example.org
  customers_subject_keywords:
    - support ticket
    - renewal

  # ---- bucket 2: partners ----
  partners_sender_emails: []
  partners_sender_domains:
    - partner-a.example.com
  partners_subject_keywords: []

  # ---- bucket 3: personal ----
  personal_sender_emails: []
  personal_sender_domains:
    - family.example.org
  personal_subject_keywords: []

  # ---- bucket 4: finance ----
  finance_sender_emails: []
  finance_sender_domains:
    - bank.example.com
    - billing.example.com
  finance_subject_keywords:
    - invoice
    - statement
    - receipt

  # ---- bucket 5: newsletters ----
  newsletter_sender_emails: []
  newsletter_sender_domains:
    - substack.com
    - beehiiv.com
  newsletter_subject_keywords:
    - newsletter
    - unsubscribe
    - digest
    - briefing

  # ---- fallback ----
  # When no rule fires, the cascade resolves to this bucket. Rename
  # if you prefer a different label, but keep exactly ONE fallback.
  no_label_bucket: no_label
---
Use only the classifier config and the message metadata.

This tool is intentionally narrow:
- only obvious sender-email rules
- only obvious sender-domain rules
- only obvious subject keywords per bucket

If no rule clearly matches, fall back to:
- `level1_classification = <no_label_bucket>`
- `level2_intent = others`

Do not infer nuanced human intent here. Nuance happens at the LLM
tier of the cascade, not at this rules tier.
---
